codex
Edits applied directly to [content/papers/stat.mech.1.md](/home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive/content/papers/stat.mech.1.md).

Summary of changes:
- Added blank-line paragraph boundaries where clearly needed (including before section headings and one clear prose break after “present review.”).
- Added KaTeX equation tags (`\tag{...}`) to ensure all in-text referenced equations are discoverable on display equations:
  - `(1-1), (1-2), (1-4), (1-5), (1-6), (1-8), (1-9), (1-12), (1-13), (1-15), (1-17), (1-19), (1-20), (1-22), (1-23), (1-24), (1-28), (1-31), (1-32), (1-33), (1-36), (1-38), (1-44), (1-45), (1-46), (1-47), (1-54), (1-55), (1-56), (1-57), (1-59), (1-60), (1-62), (1-63), (1-66)`.
- Normalized citation formatting into footnotes where citations appeared inline/bracketed, adding `[^2]`–`[^5]`.
- Kept paper content/meaning and math expressions unchanged (only structural and equation-numbering/citation markup adjustments).

Self-check:
- Paragraph boundaries use blank lines where intended in the edited areas.
- No unresolved in-text `Eq. (1-*)`/`(1-*)` references remain without a matching display-equation tag.
